investigation.title: "Microbial Observatory (ISS-MO): Indoor microbiome study of the International Space Station surfaces"
investigation.description: "Presented here is the environmental microbiome study of the International Space Station surfaces. The environmental samples were collected with the polyester wipes from eight different locations in the ISS during two consecutive sampling sessions (three months apart).

project.title: "ISS Microbial Observatory - a Genetic Approach"
project.funding: "NASA-funded, ISS-based experiment, and space biology experiment, under NNH12ZTT001N grant no. 19-12829-26"

publications.title: "Succession and persistence of microbial communities and antimicrobial resistance genes associated with International Space Station environmental surfaces."
publications.summary: "Succession and persistence of microbial communities and antimicrobial resistance genes associated with International Space Station environmental surfaces." — "10.1186/s40168-018-0585-2"
